.SS "bcftools gtcheck [\fIOPTIONS\fR] [\-g \fIgenotypes\&.vcf\&.gz\fR] \fIquery\&.vcf\&.gz\fR"
.sp
Checks sample identity\&. The program can operate in two modes\&. If the \fB\-g\fR option is given, the identity of samples from \fIquery\&.vcf\&.gz\fR is checked against the samples in the \fB\-g\fR file\&. Without the \fB\-g\fR option, multi\-sample cross\-check of samples in \fIquery\&.vcf\&.gz\fR is performed\&.
.PP
\fB\-\-distinctive\-sites\fR \fINUM[,MEM[,DIR]]\fR
.RS 4
Find sites that can distinguish between at least NUM sample pairs\&. If the number is smaller or equal to 1, it is interpreted as the fraction of pairs\&. The optional MEM string sets the maximum memory used for in\-memory sorting and DIR is the temporary directory for external sorting\&. This option requires also
\fB\-\-pairs\fR
to be given\&.
.RE
.PP
\fB\-\-dry\-run\fR
.RS 4
Stop after first record to estimate required time\&.
.RE
.PP
\fB\-e, \-\-error\-probability\fR \fIINT\fR
.RS 4
Interpret genotypes and genotype likelihoods probabilistically\&. The value of
\fIINT\fR
represents genotype quality when GT tag is used (e\&.g\&. Q=30 represents one error in 1,000 genotypes and Q=40 one error in 10,000 genotypes) and is ignored when PL tag is used (in that case an arbitrary non\-zero integer can be provided)\&. See also the
\fB\-u, \-\-use\fR
option below\&. If set to 0, the discordance equals to the number of mismatching genotypes when GT vs GT is compared\&. If performance is an issue, set to 0 for faster run but less accurate results\&.
.RE
.PP
\fB\-g, \-\-genotypes\fR \fIFILE\fR
